{"id":892009265,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"3 months, 3 weeks","timestamp":1675601591,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"51 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/892009265/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"38.9 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    bool inorder(TreeNode* root, unordered_set<int>& st, int k) {\n        if(root == NULL) return false;\n        if(st.find(k - root->val) != st.end()) return true;\n        st.insert(root->val);\n        return inorder(root->left, st, k) || inorder(root->right, st, k);\n    }\n\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        unordered_set<int> st;\n        return inorder(root, st, k);\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false}
